15 July 2015Deputy Minister of Communications (DoC), Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams will visit the North West province on Thursday, 16th July. She will participate in the Setsokotsane programme alongside Premier of the North West, Supra Mahumapelo.The Deputy Minister will lead a Youth Dialogue that will bring together youth, state entities and political principals together. The dialogue will highlight and expose entrepreneurial, academic and employment opportunities to the youth of Taung and surrounding areas. The Youth Dialogue will also be running concurrently with exhibitions by various government departments offering services and opportunities to youth. Setsokotsane is an all-inclusive radical interventionist program by Premier Supra Mahumapelo working together with his executive as well as people of the North West province to respond to the triple challenges of poverty, unemployment and inequality.Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: 16th July 2015 Time: 10:00 Venue: Mmabana Cultural Centre, Taung, North WestRSVP: Fatima Modise on 0837529707Enquiries: Mzimasi Ngqelu Cell: 0769043557 Email: mzi@doc.gov.za Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications